	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am now a gnome mage lv 10 and I found a good place to hunt from 1-3 is just outside West Freeport then once your 4 and you have a pet (I suggest getting water only but if you have extra get earth) goto North Desert of Ro by going outside East freeport gates and going straight until you zone.  BUT STAY IN THE GRASS AREA!!  There are plenty of spiderling, firebetles, moss snakes.  Save spiderling silk cause lots of starting out tailors will buy stacks of it from ya for about 8-10pp.  The othe good thing is that in the grass area there are 2 guards posted at the inn and another on the path leading towards the desert.  Do this for 4 to about 7 and once you feel froggy you can go to the begining of the desert and try to take on orc raiders and rattle snakes.  Mages are cool because of the PET.  Try to mooch Breeze, Clarity and a SOW b4 you hunt at all times this way your mana regens super fast and you can outrun everything back to the guards.  At lvl 8 I learned a good stradegy when you have sow is use a good range spell like Flame Bolt from as far away as you can and run backward and you can try to get another hit on the moster while he tries to catch up and then have your pet attack now youve gotten 3 hits on him and hes got none.  Then get about 1 or two more majic hits on the moster and report your pet and see what percent hit points he has left.  When he has 55-65 percent move on the opposite side of the monster so your pet and you are on opposite sides and melee attack the moster untill your pet reports better health and repeat.  With mana and sow buffs you can take on yellows and feel confident and if you get in trouble leave our PET to die and run to the Guards.  But one thing i learned once I started hunting in the beginning of the desert WATCH OUT FOR MADMEN for some reason mabye my bad luck whenever I had a Madman follow me the GUARDS WOULDNT TO JACK SHIAT.  I had to zone to get rid of them.<br><br>Seriallova<br>lvl 10 Mage<br>Erolissi Marr Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
