	   <tr><td colspan=2>What pet were you using? If it was the fire or air pet then you would definately have a problem, as you probably won't be able to break the camp with those pets. I suggest using the earth or water pet to kil all 3 at once. You will need to keep resummoning your pet until it cons yellow to you (if you are level 4). If you are level 5 then make sure it cons white/black. Once you have summoned and level 5 earth or water pet give him a two-handed weapon.<br><br>Now the pull.  You need to move around the camp and con all the kobolds. Once you have found the kobold that is the lowest level, use your burn spell to pull him out. When you pull him all 3 kobolds will come at you at once. You need to tank for your pet for a little bit, or else it will not survive. Once your pet has killed the lowest level kobold, which should be really quick since you alredy hit it with a burn spell and it is using a two-handed weapon, you need to back up and let your pet tank. Start casting your burn spell on the the kobold that your pet is currently attacking, this way that kobold will die quickly and you and your pet will be left with one kobold to deal with.<br><br>With that one kobold left you should go and tank for your pet a little bit, because it will be severely weakened by now. Make sure you don't get yourself killed though. If you DO die, then run back to the kobold camp as quick as possible, summon another pet, and finish killing the kobolds before the rest of them respawn. That way if you die, you will have killed at least one kobold first, and when you go back you will only have to deal with two. And if you do die breaking the camp, don't worry, you lose barely any exp. at your level.<br><br>Once you have the camp broken it is really easy to hold. Just start killing kobolds as soon as they pop up. Time your killings though, so that you won't have kobolds coming back up at the same time. Also, on the ledge to the left of the camp is another kobold. Once you have broken the camp and have it secured, you will be able to kill him and keep the camp secured at the same time. I hope that helps!<br><br>If you have anymore questions email me.<br><br>tim_gerber@yahoo.com<br><br>Former EQ Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
